Instruction: Sequentially measure the voltage at the input terminals and across the indicator LED in each of Control Modules 3 through 8, with each switch in the ON position. Continue until a module is found that does not properly pass voltage or whose indicator does not show the expected voltage drop. This will help localize a potential open circuit in the string of series-connected control modules.
